{"key":"processedPost-18426389","value":{"id":18426389,"first":18425218,"last":18429475,"when":1371383268,"utime":"06/16/13 02:47 PM","content":"<blockquote>Quote:<br /><b>mr.muscles said:</b><br />I don't have a shotgun fruiting chamber, I have a fruiting chamber with a air pump instead is this still an issue?<br /></blockquote><br /><br />This is your problem.&nbsp; Don't run a sealed terrarium.&nbsp; The greenhouse effect from your light is overheating it.&nbsp; Build a <a href=\"http://www.mushroomvideos.com/Terrarium-Tek\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer noopener\">shotgun terrarium</a>.&nbsp; If you need to cool it, lay a damp towel over the shotgun terrarium and then point a fan at it.&nbsp; The evaporative cooling as the moisture leaves the towel will draw heat out of the fruiting chamber.<br /><br />Disregard bad advice to turn the light off.&nbsp; It's important for proper growth and development of the mushrooms unless you have a bright window nearby.<br />RR","title":"Re: Terrarium is getting too hot - please help"}}